snippet.textDisplay: May I ask you a question? Today, an American invited me and my friends to watch your program. Every time "wuhan" and "China" appeared in the program, he would laugh out loud. I have no English listening ability, so I can't understand your program. My friends and I were embarrassed by his laughter, feeling that he was mocking us, and the American asked one of my friends from hubei how he felt after watching your video. To be honest, although some netizens are of poor quality, no TV variety show in China dares to make fun of other countries' disasters. So I don't know if it's a cultural difference or if the American does have a huge grudge against us?
